  "prompt": "Is leave letter necessary for tourist visa?",
  "response": "Yes, a leave letter can be necessary when applying for a tourist visa. A leave letter, also known as a leave approval letter or a no-objection certificate (NOC) from your employer, indicates that you have been granted leave for the period of your intended travel and that your employer does not object to your travel plans. This document can help establish your intent to return to your home country after your trip, which is a requirement for many tourist visa applications.\n\nIt's important to check the specific requirements of the country you are applying to, as different countries may have different documentation requirements for tourist visas. Additionally, providing a detailed itinerary, proof of accommodation, financial statements, and other relevant documents can also support your visa application.",
